All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    AsciiView
    The command line view for this calculator.
    BadTypeException
    Thrown by methods in the Entry class to indicate that the wrong getter was called on a given Entry object.
    CalcController
    The controller.
    CalculatorFactory
    A calculator factory.
    CalculatorInterface
    This is an interface for classes that can evaluate some mathematical expression.
    Driver
    The entry point for this program.
    Entry
    The Entry class represents an entry in the calculator, corresponding to a number, mathematical symbol, or string of tokens.
    InvalidExpressionException
    Thrown by methods that implement the Calculator interface to indicate that the expression evaluated was not indeed a valid mathematical expression.
    JavaFxView
    This is the JavaFX view class for the calculator, filled by the FXML loader at run time.
    LeafNode
    A LeafNode represents a leaf in the syntax tree built up when evaluating an expression using Reverse Polish notation.
    NumStack
    This class represents a stack of numbers.
    Observer
    A functional interface used to implement the Observer pattern.
    Operator
    This interface represents some mathematical operator.
    OperatorNode
    An OperatorNode is a node that has two child LeafNodes.
    Operators
    This is an enum of members that implement the Operator interface.
    OpStack
    A stack of operators.
    RevPolishCalc
    This class evaluates mathematical expressions given in reverse Polish notation.
    Stack
    The Stack class represents a last-in-first-out stack of Entry objects.
    StandardCalc
    A calculator class to evaluate standard/infix expressions.
    SumVisitor
    A SumVisitor visits LeafNodes and OperatorNodes to evaluate a postfix syntax tree, setting the answer attribute to the result of an evaluated expression.
    Symbol
    The Symbol enum represents the non-number tokens allowed in an expression in this calculator.
    Type
    The Type enum represents the types an Entry can represent.
    ViewInterface
    Represents a view in this calculator.
    Visitable
    A Visitable class can be visited by some Visitor, which in turn may perform some algorithm on the Visitable.
    Visitor
    A Visitor can visit any Visitable node, and usually perform some algorithm on it.
